# ft_printf

## Description

The goal of this project is to recreate the standard C function `printf()`.  
ft_printf handles formatted output and supports these conversion specifiers: %c, %s, %p, %d / %i, %u, %x / %X, %%.  

This project teaches handling of variadic functions and formatted output in C.

## Algorithm & Data Structures

The program parses the format string character by character. When `%` is found, it determines the conversion type and prints the corresponding argument using `va_list`.  

Data structures used:  
- va_list for variable arguments  
- Standard C types and arrays (no complex structures required)

